content:
Switch Between a 12- or 9-Column Dashboard Layout

Both the 12-column and 9-column dashboard gives you plenty of room to lay out data in easy-to-consume ways.

Available in: Lightning Experience, Essentials, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions
User permissions needed:
Create and Customize Dashboards (for both layouts)
Manage Dynamic Dashboards (for dynamic dashboards)

Any dashboard can have 12 or 9 columns.

When switching to a 9-column dashboard from a 12-column dashboard, the dashboard updates its layout.
When switching to a 12-column dashboard from a 9-column dashboard, three empty columns appear on the right side of the dashboard.

Create or edit a dashboard:
Open the Properties menu by clicking 
Under Dashboard Grid Size, choose the number of columns
Click Save
title: Switching Between 12-Column and 9-Column Dashboards in Salesforce
